NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setProtocolFee(uint256).details: Collects fees first in order to not apply new protocol fee to previously accrued fees.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.amount0: Amount of token0 contract needs to send
params.amount1: Amount of token1 contracts needs to send

withdrawPartial(uint256,uint256).details: Withdraws the portion evenly from the main position, secondary position and idle balancesAssumes collectFees has been called right before this call

addVestingPosition(uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Creates a new position which is vested over time to the Vault depositors

balances().notice: Returns the current balances of the Strategy

changeFeeRecipient(address).notice: Changes the fee recipient to new address

changePositionWidth(uint24).notice: Changes the Main position's width and triggers a rebalance

changeRebalancer(address).notice: Changes the rebalancer to new address

checkPoolActivity().notice: Checks the pool prices in consecutive observations, up to TWAP ago.

collectFees().notice: Collects all outstanding position feesIn case there's ongoing vested position, collects the already vested part of it.

compound().notice: Adds as much as possible of the idle funds within the positions

feeRecipient().notice: the address which receives the accrued protocol fees

getMainPosition().notice: View function to get the main position

getSecondaryPosition().notice: View function to get the secondary position

getVestingPosition().notice: View function to get the Vesting position

idleBalances().notice: The funds within the contract which are not currently added as liquidity

lastRebalance().notice: The timestamp of the last rebalance

maxObservationDeviation().notice: The maximum deviation allowed between two consecutive observations

ongoingVestingPosition().notice: Whether there's a position being vested currently.

pool().notice: the address of the underlying pool

positionWidth().notice: the width of the main position

price().notice: Returns the token0/token1 spot price in 1e30 precision

protocolFee().notice: The current protocol fee, in basis points (10_000 = 100%)

rebalance().notice: Removes liquidity from old positions, calculates new ones and adds liquidity to them

rebalanceInterval().notice: The minimum time interval that needs to have passed since last rebalance, in order to trigger a new one.

setMaxObservationDeviation(uint24).notice: Sets the new max accepted deviation between two consecutive observations

setProtocolFee(uint256).notice: Sets new protocol fee. Capped at 15%.

setRebalanceInterval(uint256).notice: Sets the new minimum interval that needs to have passed since last rebalance, in order to rebalance again

setTickTwapDeviation(uint24).notice: Sets the max accepted deviation between pool's spot price and TWAP price

tickSpacing().notice: The tickspacing of the underlying pool

tickTwapDeviation().notice: The maximum deviation allowed between TWAP price and spot price

token0().notice: The address of the first token in the pool

token1().notice: The address of the second token in the pool

twap().notice: The TWAP interval based on which we get the underlying pool's price

uniswapV3MintCallback(uint256,uint256,by.notice: Callback function of the underlying Uniswap pool

vault().notice: Address of the vault utilizing this Strategy

withdrawPartial(uint256,uint256).notice: Withdraws a user's portion of the assets
